<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="21.[189,310,813,839]" box="[189,310,813,839]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,310,813,839]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,813,839]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[188,1399,860,1104]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<taxonomicName authority="Gustafsson &amp; Najer &amp; Zou &amp; Bush, 2022" authorityName="Gustafsson &amp; Najer &amp; Zou &amp; Bush" authorityYear="2022" box="[189,411,860,886]" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Guimaraesiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psocodea" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ixi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[189,411,860,886]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Guimaraesiella ixi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[421,515,861,887]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is not particularly similar to any other species of 
<taxonomicName box="[1126,1309,860,886]" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Guimaraesiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psocodea" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1126,1309,860,886]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Guimaraesiella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
known from bulbuls, and can be separated from all other species by the following combination of characters: male tergopleurites IV–V without 
<emphasis box="[588,622,934,959]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">tps</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[638,725,933,959]" captionStart="Figs 29–30" captionStartId="22.[189,241,1962,1988]" captionTargetBox="[387,1202,797,1915]" captionTargetId="figure-137@22.[383,1204,793,1918]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Figs 29–30. Guimaraesiella ixi sp. nov. 29. Male habitus, dorsal and ventral views. 30. Female habitus, dorsal and ventral views." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6358697" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6358697/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
); proximal mesosome narrow distally (
<figureCitation box="[1180,1267,933,959]" captionStart="Figs 31–35" captionStartId="23.[189,241,1848,1874]" captionTargetBox="[354,1228,577,1770]" captionTargetId="figure-105@23.[351,1237,571,1778]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="Figs 31–35. Guimaraesiella ixi sp. nov. 31. Male head, dorsal and ventral views. 32. Male genitalia, dorsal view. 33. Male paramere, dorsal view. 34. Male mesosome, ventral view. 35. Female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6358701" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6358701/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Fig. 34</figureCitation>
); gonopore slenderly crescent shaped (
<figureCitation box="[508,597,969,995]" captionStart="Figs 31–35" captionStartId="23.[189,241,1848,1874]" captionTargetBox="[354,1228,577,1770]" captionTargetId="figure-105@23.[351,1237,571,1778]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="Figs 31–35. Guimaraesiella ixi sp. nov. 31. Male head, dorsal and ventral views. 32. Male genitalia, dorsal view. 33. Male paramere, dorsal view. 34. Male mesosome, ventral view. 35. Female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6358701" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6358701/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Fig. 34</figureCitation>
); dorsal preantennal suture reaching 
<emphasis box="[1038,1079,969,995]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">ads</emphasis>
and lateral margin of head (
<figureCitation box="[199,286,1005,1031]" captionStart="Figs 31–35" captionStartId="23.[189,241,1848,1874]" captionTargetBox="[354,1228,577,1770]" captionTargetId="figure-105@23.[351,1237,571,1778]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="Figs 31–35. Guimaraesiella ixi sp. nov. 31. Male head, dorsal and ventral views. 32. Male genitalia, dorsal view. 33. Male paramere, dorsal view. 34. Male mesosome, ventral view. 35. Female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6358701" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6358701/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Fig. 31</figureCitation>
); male tergopleurite VI without 
<emphasis box="[665,706,1006,1031]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">aps</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[722,810,1005,1031]" captionStart="Figs 29–30" captionStartId="22.[189,241,1962,1988]" captionTargetBox="[387,1202,797,1915]" captionTargetId="figure-137@22.[383,1204,793,1918]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Figs 29–30. Guimaraesiella ixi sp. nov. 29. Male habitus, dorsal and ventral views. 30. Female habitus, dorsal and ventral views." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6358697" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6358697/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
); abdominal segment IV with 2 
<emphasis box="[1189,1215,1006,1031]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">ps</emphasis>
on each side in both sexes (
<figureCitation box="[330,419,1041,1068]" captionStart="Figs 29–30" captionStartId="22.[189,241,1962,1988]" captionTargetBox="[387,1202,797,1915]" captionTargetId="figure-137@22.[383,1204,793,1918]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Figs 29–30. Guimaraesiella ixi sp. nov. 29. Male habitus, dorsal and ventral views. 30. Female habitus, dorsal and ventral views." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6358697" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6358697/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
); proximal mesosome slender (
<figureCitation box="[789,878,1041,1068]" captionStart="Figs 31–35" captionStartId="23.[189,241,1848,1874]" captionTargetBox="[354,1228,577,1770]" captionTargetId="figure-105@23.[351,1237,571,1778]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="Figs 31–35. Guimaraesiella ixi sp. nov. 31. Male head, dorsal and ventral views. 32. Male genitalia, dorsal view. 33. Male paramere, dorsal view. 34. Male mesosome, ventral view. 35. Female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6358701" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6358701/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Fig. 34</figureCitation>
); ventral sclerite of mesosome with anterior thickening (
<figureCitation box="[330,418,1078,1104]" captionStart="Figs 24–28" captionStartId="20.[189,241,1926,1952]" captionTargetBox="[356,1235,639,1874]" captionTargetId="figure-139@20.[345,1242,634,1880]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Figs 24–28. Guimaraesiella lorica sp. nov. 24. Male head, dorsal and ventral views. 25. Male genitalia, dorsal view. 26. Male paramere, dorsal view. 27. Male mesosome, ventral view. 28. Female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6358693" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6358693/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Fig. 27</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
