</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[185,1400,1709,2025]" box="[234,366,1709,1735]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[234,366,1709,1735]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Both sexes</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[185,1400,1709,2025]" lastBlockId="22.[189,1398,265,327]" lastPageId="22" lastPageNumber="23" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
Head pentagonal(
<figureCitation box="[396,479,1745,1771]" captionStart="Figs 31–35" captionStartId="23.[189,241,1848,1874]" captionTargetBox="[354,1228,577,1770]" captionTargetId="figure-105@23.[351,1237,571,1778]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="Figs 31–35. Guimaraesiella ixi sp. nov. 31. Male head, dorsal and ventral views. 32. Male genitalia, dorsal view. 33. Male paramere, dorsal view. 34. Male mesosome, ventral view. 35. Female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6358701" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6358701/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Fig.31</figureCitation>
), lateral margins of preantennal head more or less straight, frons slightly concave. Marginal carina slender, gradually narrowing anteriorly, median margin only slightly undulating. Dorsal anterior plate narrowing posteriorly, with shallowly concave anterior margin and convex lateral margins. Ventral anterior plate short, bowl-shaped with slightly concave anterior margin. Dorsal preantennal suture reaches 
<emphasis box="[367,408,1890,1916]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">ads</emphasis>
and lateral margins of head. Preantennal nodi extended medianly. Head chaetotaxy as in 
<figureCitation box="[253,338,1926,1952]" captionStart="Figs 31–35" captionStartId="23.[189,241,1848,1874]" captionTargetBox="[354,1228,577,1770]" captionTargetId="figure-105@23.[351,1237,571,1778]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="Figs 31–35. Guimaraesiella ixi sp. nov. 31. Male head, dorsal and ventral views. 32. Male genitalia, dorsal view. 33. Male paramere, dorsal view. 34. Male mesosome, ventral view. 35. Female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6358701" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6358701/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Fig. 31</figureCitation>
. Coni reach beyond distal margin of scapes. Lateral margins of postantennal head slightly convex. Temples sharply rounded. Temporal marginal carina slender, only slightly irregular. Thoracic and abdominal segments as in 
<figureCitation box="[569,707,1998,2024]" captionStart="Figs 29–30" captionStartId="22.[189,241,1962,1988]" captionTargetBox="[387,1202,797,1915]" captionTargetId="figure-137@22.[383,1204,793,1918]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Figs 29–30. Guimaraesiella ixi sp. nov. 29. Male habitus, dorsal and ventral views. 30. Female habitus, dorsal and ventral views." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6358697" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6358697/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Figs 29–30</figureCitation>
. Base pigmentation very faint, most of body translucent, except preantennal and preocular nodi, gular plate, proepimera, metepisterna and lateral sections of tergopleurites pale brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[188,1399,367,646]" box="[234,298,367,393]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[234,298,367,393]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Male</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[188,1399,367,646]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
Thoracic and abdominal chaetotaxy as in 
<figureCitation box="[713,806,403,429]" captionStart="Figs 29–30" captionStartId="22.[189,241,1962,1988]" captionTargetBox="[387,1202,797,1915]" captionTargetId="figure-137@22.[383,1204,793,1918]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Figs 29–30. Guimaraesiella ixi sp. nov. 29. Male habitus, dorsal and ventral views. 30. Female habitus, dorsal and ventral views." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6358697" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6358697/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
. Basal apodeme short, constricted distally from mid-length (
<figureCitation box="[336,427,439,465]" captionStart="Figs 31–35" captionStartId="23.[189,241,1848,1874]" captionTargetBox="[354,1228,577,1770]" captionTargetId="figure-105@23.[351,1237,571,1778]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="Figs 31–35. Guimaraesiella ixi sp. nov. 31. Male head, dorsal and ventral views. 32. Male genitalia, dorsal view. 33. Male paramere, dorsal view. 34. Male mesosome, ventral view. 35. Female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6358701" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6358701/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Fig. 32</figureCitation>
). Proximal mesosome trapezoidal (
<figureCitation box="[851,942,439,465]" captionStart="Figs 31–35" captionStartId="23.[189,241,1848,1874]" captionTargetBox="[354,1228,577,1770]" captionTargetId="figure-105@23.[351,1237,571,1778]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="Figs 31–35. Guimaraesiella ixi sp. nov. 31. Male head, dorsal and ventral views. 32. Male genitalia, dorsal view. 33. Male paramere, dorsal view. 34. Male mesosome, ventral view. 35. Female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6358701" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6358701/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Fig. 34</figureCitation>
). Ventral sclerite slender, anterior end rounded, not thickened, not reaching anterior margin of proximal mesosome. Mesosomal lobes rounded triangular; 3 
<emphasis box="[346,406,512,537]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">ames</emphasis>
sensilla on each side, distal seta on each side apparently longer than two proximal setae; 2 
<emphasis box="[284,344,548,573]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">pmes</emphasis>
microsetae on lateral margins of mesosome. Gonopore deeply crescent shaped. Parameral heads as in 
<figureCitation box="[322,409,583,609]" captionStart="Figs 31–35" captionStartId="23.[189,241,1848,1874]" captionTargetBox="[354,1228,577,1770]" captionTargetId="figure-105@23.[351,1237,571,1778]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="Figs 31–35. Guimaraesiella ixi sp. nov. 31. Male head, dorsal and ventral views. 32. Male genitalia, dorsal view. 33. Male paramere, dorsal view. 34. Male mesosome, ventral view. 35. Female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6358701" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6358701/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Fig. 33</figureCitation>
. Parameral blades stout, in shape of hunting knife, narrowing only distally; 
<emphasis box="[1288,1367,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">pst1–2</emphasis>
as in 
<figureCitation box="[218,305,619,645]" captionStart="Figs 31–35" captionStartId="23.[189,241,1848,1874]" captionTargetBox="[354,1228,577,1770]" captionTargetId="figure-105@23.[351,1237,571,1778]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="Figs 31–35. Guimaraesiella ixi sp. nov. 31. Male head, dorsal and ventral views. 32. Male genitalia, dorsal view. 33. Male paramere, dorsal view. 34. Male mesosome, ventral view. 35. Female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6358701" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6358701/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Fig. 33</figureCitation>
. Measurements as in 
<tableCitation box="[556,644,619,645]" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="9.[185,254,545,573]" captionTargetBox="[185,1932,730,1738]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Table 1 (continued on next two pages). Measurements of the species described here. Means (in brackets) only included for samples sizes&gt;10. Abbreviations: AW = abdominal width; HL = head length; HW = head width; N = number; PRW = prothoracic width; PTW = pterothoracic width; TL = total length. Genus abbreviations: Br. = Brueelia; Gu. = Guimaraesiella; Po. = Philopteroides. For additional measurements for the species of Philopteroides Mey, 2004, see Table 2." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/3AFA6662DC70CD51FF08806B52E7FD0B" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" tableUuid="3AFA6662DC70CD51FF08806B52E7FD0B">Table 1</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6358697" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6358697" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6358697/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" startId="22.[189,241,1962,1988]" targetBox="[387,1202,797,1915]" targetPageId="22">
<paragraph blockId="22.[189,1398,1962,2024]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,329,1962,1988]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Figs 29–30.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Gustafsson &amp; Najer &amp; Zou &amp; Bush, 2022" authorityName="Gustafsson &amp; Najer &amp; Zou &amp; Bush" authorityYear="2022" box="[336,555,1962,1988]" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Guimaraesiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psocodea" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ixi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[336,555,1962,1988]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Guimaraesiella ixi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[562,652,1963,1989]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[659,688,1962,1988]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">29</emphasis>
. Male habitus, dorsal and ventral views. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1169,1198,1962,1988]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">30</emphasis>
. Female habitus, dorsal and ventral views.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="23.[189,1399,265,432]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[234,325,265,291]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Female</emphasis>
Thoracic and abdominal chaetotaxy as in 
<figureCitation box="[689,778,300,326]" captionStart="Figs 29–30" captionStartId="22.[189,241,1962,1988]" captionTargetBox="[387,1202,797,1915]" captionTargetId="figure-137@22.[383,1204,793,1918]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Figs 29–30. Guimaraesiella ixi sp. nov. 29. Male habitus, dorsal and ventral views. 30. Female habitus, dorsal and ventral views." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6358697" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6358697/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Fig. 30</figureCitation>
. Subgenital plate broad in distal end (
<figureCitation box="[1234,1323,299,326]" captionStart="Figs 31–35" captionStartId="23.[189,241,1848,1874]" captionTargetBox="[354,1228,577,1770]" captionTargetId="figure-105@23.[351,1237,571,1778]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="Figs 31–35. Guimaraesiella ixi sp. nov. 31. Male head, dorsal and ventral views. 32. Male genitalia, dorsal view. 33. Male paramere, dorsal view. 34. Male mesosome, ventral view. 35. Female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6358701" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6358701/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Fig. 35</figureCitation>
), with blunt and broad lateral submarginal extensions. Vulval margin curved, with 3–4 short, slender 
<emphasis box="[1303,1349,336,361]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">vms</emphasis>
and 5–7 short, thorn-like 
<emphasis box="[436,472,371,396]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">vss</emphasis>
on each side; 5–6 short, slender 
<emphasis box="[854,893,371,396]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">vos</emphasis>
on each side of subgenital plate; distal 1–2 
<emphasis box="[189,228,406,431]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">vos</emphasis>
median to 
<emphasis box="[359,395,406,431]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">vss</emphasis>
. Measurements as in 
<tableCitation box="[650,738,405,431]" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="9.[185,254,545,573]" captionTargetBox="[185,1932,730,1738]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Table 1 (continued on next two pages). Measurements of the species described here. Means (in brackets) only included for samples sizes&gt;10. Abbreviations: AW = abdominal width; HL = head length; HW = head width; N = number; PRW = prothoracic width; PTW = pterothoracic width; TL = total length. Genus abbreviations: Br. = Brueelia; Gu. = Guimaraesiella; Po. = Philopteroides. For additional measurements for the species of Philopteroides Mey, 2004, see Table 2." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/3AFA6662DC70CD51FF08806B52E7FD0B" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" tableUuid="3AFA6662DC70CD51FF08806B52E7FD0B">Table 1</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
